  "texts": [
    "Producing such subsets of gene sets can be done by simply searching the table titles for terms that match named entities such as protein kinases or transcription factors.",
    "Indeed, we identified 4525 gene sets that contain named human kinases, and 8078 gene sets that contain named transcription factors in the table titles.",
    "444 kinase names and 1121 transcription factor names are unique in these collections of gene sets (Fig. 2a, Supplementary Data 2, 3).",
    "Similarly, we identified 4443 gene sets that contain named cell lines, and 6268 gene sets that contain cell types or tissues in table titles, with 450 and 670 unique terms, respectively (Fig. 2b).",
    "In addition, 5560 sets had the term \"down\" and 6677 had the term \"up\" in their table titles (Fig. 2c)."
  ],
